<title>SOUTH KOREA: LG Elec unveils new hand-held computer.</title>
<headline>LG Elec unveils new hand-held computer.</headline>
<dateline>SEOUL 1996-11-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Korea's LG Electronics Inc, a unit of LG Group, said on Tuesday it had developed what it claimed is the world's smallest hand-held computer in a technical tie-up with Microsoft Corp.</p>
<p>LG's GP40M computer adopts Hitachi SH-3 as the central processing unit, equivalent in capacity to an Intel Corp's 486 processor, a LG statement said.</p>
<p>The new device weighs 340 grams and adopts Microsoft Windows CE as the disk operating system, it said.</p>
<p>LG plans to sell the computers at around $500 per unit on the U.S. market and launch domestic sales in April next year for about 400,000 won per unit, it added.</p>
<p>-- Seoul Newsroom (822) 727-5646</p>
